<br>
This also applies heavily to the Ragefire problem with SOTU v ADD thing.  <br>
<br>
The rules state something like:<br>
<br>
&quot;whoever is there with a sizable force first gets the pop&quot;<br>
<br>
But this is gonna cause problems, flames, bitterness, arguments....<br>
<br>
Then there is the other side of the argument<br>
<br>
&quot;Well I have been camping X mob for 18 hours and a force will be here shortly&quot;<br>
<br>
What is defined as shortly 10 mins ? 10 hours ? 10 weeks ? <br>
<br>
I have been in Karnor with my cleirc before and a guy was calling VSR for the best part of 3 hours, every 5 frigging minutes.  I was tempted to go get a force to kill it just to shut him up.  <br>
<br>
Verant's rules suck ! because you will tread on toes if you follow these stringently. <br>
<br>
I am not offering a solution to this, but I feel that some benefit of the doubt should go to the person camping it WITHIN REASON.  I know that Paeg of Wraith was camping Ragefire for the best part of 36 hours on and off(swapping people etc), I personally would not have been happy should Ragefire have popped and guild B just said, thank you very much we will take that spawn now.<br>
<br>
If however, it has popped and contact had been made with Paeg who said there are guildies coming over shortly...and there was not a sizable force within 2 hours, I would say Guild B has every right to go in and drop the mob.  <br>
 <br>
We are all on the same team at the end of the day and we are here to work with one another not against each other.<br>
