<br>
I guess we're playing different games. I really see no point to playing EQ if I'm not playing with my friends.<br>
<br>
Lets face it. EQ is a social game. Though there may be competition to get what you want, in the end game you need help... generally lots of help (from people you may have helped), to get the &quot;phat lewts&quot;.<br>
<br>
Everyone has different reasons for playing, but - and this is my opinion - if you aren't playing for the social aspect, you are missing out on 9/10ths of the game.<br>
<br>
That said, and getting back to the point of this post: Ambition is a dangerous thing. If getting a piece of pixelated ego-stroking form of power is more important than being nice to people in general... you're just missing out. And it might burn you harder than you think later.<br>
<br>
